OL,3,CGary Lineker says 'right time' to
OL,4,Cleave Match of the Day
OL,6,FGary Lineker has said it was "an
OL,7,Fabsolute joy and privilege" to host
OL,8,FMatch of the Day for over two decades
OL,9,Fbut it was "the right time" for him to
OL,10,Fleave.
OL,12,FThe 63-year-old former England striker
OL,13,Fwill step down as the host of Match of
OL,14,Fthe Day (MOTD) at the end of the
OL,15,Fseason as the BBC plans to make
OL,16,Fchanges to the programme.
OL,18,FHowever, he will continue to present
OL,19,Fthe broadcaster's coverage of the FA
OL,20,FCup in the 2025/26 season and the
OL,21,FWorld Cup in 2026.
